EXPR_LINE_USER

Method Detail

parse

public void parse(String _url,
                  String _content)

Parses all common workspace object specific URL values. This includes:

  • AbstractWorkspaceObject_mxJPO.name
  • hidden flag
  • user for which this workspace object is visible

If an _url is included in IGNORED_URLS, this URL is ignored.

Overrides:
parse in class AbstractVisualWorkspaceObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_url - URL to parse
_content - content of the URL to parse
See Also:
IGNORED_URLS

prepare

public void prepare(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)
             throws matrix.util.MatrixException
Because the table export does not set the correct active flag, a MQL print on the table is made and evaluated for the string " active".

Overrides:

write

public void write(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                  Appendable _out)
           throws IOException

Writes all table specific values to the TCL update file _out. This includes:

  • table columns

Because the units definition must behind the user definition, a regular expression is used to replace the user definition by a concatenation of the user with the units definition. As units "points" are used.

Overrides:
write in class AbstractVisualWorkspaceObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_out - appendable instance to the TCL update file
Throws:
IOException - if the TCL update code could not written
See Also:
EXPR_LINE_USER, REPLACE_LINE_USER_WITH_UNITS
